    "We hypothesize that this is because the all-or-nothing reward design encourages the model to focus on meeting all criteria in the rubric, rather than just a subset of them, which is consistent with the instruction following benchmark evaluation protocols.",
    "Additionally the fractional rubric reward design may introduce more noise in the reward signal as the rubric verifier may not be perfectly accurate in evaluating each criterion individually.",
    "We leave a more comprehensive study of reward design for future work.",
    "We also conduct a qualitative analysis on the impact of additional criteria for reward hacking prevention mentioned in Section 4.4.",
    "We find that these criteria can effectively mitigate reward hacking issues during RL training."
